Part soda shoppe, part thrift store, part mini diner.
The thrift store portions have some great stuff.
A great vintage fashion section, LOTS of records (your parents remember those, kids), and some great jewelry.
The mini diner area has, what I believe is all the original booths and counter.
The booths are kind of small, and though they all have jukeboxes on them, they all seemed to be out of order while we were here.
They serve very simple diner food (hot dogs, hamburgers, fries, grilled cheese, etc), but their real specialty is their sodas and ice cream floats.
There is a pretty large selection of sodas to choose from.
